#: ../../language/error-handling.md:1
msgid "Error handling"
msgstr "エラーハンドリング"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:3
msgid ""
"Error handling has always been at core of our language design. In the "
"following we'll be explaining how error handling is done in MoonBit. We "
"assume you have some prior knowledge of MoonBit, if not, please checkout [A "
"tour of MoonBit](../tutorial/tour.md)."
msgstr ""
"エラーハンドリングは、私たちの言語設計の中核です。以下では、MoonBit でのエラーハンドリングの方法を説明します。MoonBit "
"の基本的な知識があることを前提としています。まだの場合は [A tour of MoonBit](../tutorial/tour.md) "
"を参照してください。"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:8
msgid "Error Types"
msgstr "エラー型"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:10
msgid ""
"In MoonBit, all the error values can be represented by the `Error` type, a "
"generalized error type."
msgstr "MoonBit では、すべてのエラー値を汎用エラー型である `Error` 型で表現できます。"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:13
msgid ""
"However, an `Error` cannot be constructed directly. A concrete error type "
"must be defined, in the following forms:"
msgstr "ただし、`Error` は直接構築できません。次の形式で具体的なエラー型を定義する必要があります:"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:16
msgid ""
"suberror E1 { E1(Int) } // error type E1 has one constructor E1 with an Int "
"payload\n"
"\n"
"suberror E2 // error type E2 has one constructor E2 with no payload\n"
"\n"
"suberror E3 { // error type E3 has three constructors like a normal enum "
"type\n"
"  A\n"
"  B(Int, x~ : String)\n"
"  C(mut x~ : String, Char, y~ : Bool)\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"suberror E1 { E1(Int) } // error type E1 has one constructor E1 with an Int "
"payload\n"
"\n"
"suberror E2 // error type E2 has one constructor E2 with no payload\n"
"\n"
"suberror E3 { // error type E3 has three constructors like a normal enum "
"type\n"
"  A\n"
"  B(Int, x~ : String)\n"
"  C(mut x~ : String, Char, y~ : Bool)\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:24
msgid ""
"The older `suberror A B` syntax is deprecated. Use `suberror A { A(B) }` "
"instead."
msgstr "古い `suberror A B` 構文は非推奨です。代わりに `suberror A { A(B) }` を使ってください。"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:27
msgid ""
"The error types can be promoted to the `Error` type automatically, and "
"pattern matched back:"
msgstr "これらのエラー型は自動的に `Error` 型へ昇格でき、パターンマッチで取り出せます:"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:30
msgid ""
"suberror CustomError { CustomError(UInt) }\n"
"\n"
"test {\n"
"  let e : Error = CustomError(42)\n"
"  guard e is CustomError(m)\n"
"  assert_eq(m, 42)\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"suberror CustomError { CustomError(UInt) }\n"
"\n"
"test {\n"
"  let e : Error = CustomError(42)\n"
"  guard e is CustomError(m)\n"
"  assert_eq(m, 42)\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:36
msgid ""
"Since the type `Error` can include multiple error types, pattern matching on"
" the `Error` type must use the wildcard `_` to match all error types. For "
"example,"
msgstr ""
"`Error` 型には複数のエラー型を含められるため、`Error` 型に対するパターンマッチでは、すべてのエラー型に対応するためにワイルドカード "
"`_` を使う必要があります。例えば:"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:39
msgid ""
"fn f(e : Error) -> Unit {\n"
"  match e {\n"
"    E2 => println(\"E2\")\n"
"    A => println(\"A\")\n"
"    B(i, x~) => println(\"B(\\{i}, \\{x})\")\n"
"    _ => println(\"unknown error\")\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"fn f(e : Error) -> Unit {\n"
"  match e {\n"
"    E2 => println(\"E2\")\n"
"    A => println(\"A\")\n"
"    B(i, x~) => println(\"B(\\{i}, \\{x})\")\n"
"    _ => println(\"unknown error\")\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:45
msgid ""
"The `Error` is meant to be used where no concrete error type is needed, or a"
" catch-all for all kinds of sub-errors is needed."
msgstr "`Error` は、具体的なエラー型が不要な場面や、あらゆる種類のサブエラーを一括で扱いたい場面で使うことを想定しています。"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:48
msgid "Failure"
msgstr "Failure"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:50
msgid "A builtin error type is `Failure`."
msgstr "組み込みエラー型として `Failure` があります。"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:52
msgid ""
"There's a handly `fail` function, which is merely a constructor with a pre-"
"defined output template for showing both the error and the source location. "
"In practice, `fail` is always preferred over `Failure`."
msgstr ""
"便利な `fail` "
"関数もあります。これはエラーとソース位置の両方を表示するための定義済み出力テンプレートを持つ、実質的にはコンストラクタです。実際には `Failure`"
" より `fail` を常に優先して使います。"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:58
msgid ""
"#callsite(autofill(loc))\n"
"pub fn[T] fail(msg : String, loc~ : SourceLoc) -> T raise Failure {\n"
"  raise Failure(\"FAILED: \\{loc} \\{msg}\")\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"#callsite(autofill(loc))\n"
"pub fn[T] fail(msg : String, loc~ : SourceLoc) -> T raise Failure {\n"
"  raise Failure(\"FAILED: \\{loc} \\{msg}\")\n"
"}"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:66
msgid "Throwing Errors"
msgstr "エラーの送出"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:68
msgid ""
"The keyword `raise` is used to interrupt the function execution and return "
"an error."
msgstr "`raise` キーワードは、関数の実行を中断してエラーを返すために使います。"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:71
msgid ""
"The type declaration of a function can use `raise` with an Error type to "
"indicate that the function might raise an error during an execution. For "
"example, the following function `div` might return an error of type "
"`DivError`:"
msgstr ""
"関数の型宣言では、`raise` とエラー型を組み合わせて、その関数が実行中にエラーを送出する可能性があることを示せます。例えば次の `div` 関数は"
" `DivError` 型のエラーを返す可能性があります:"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:75
msgid ""
"suberror DivError { DivError(String) }\n"
"\n"
"fn div(x : Int, y : Int) -> Int raise DivError {\n"
"  if y == 0 {\n"
"    raise DivError(\"division by zero\")\n"
"  }\n"
"  x / y\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"suberror DivError { DivError(String) }\n"
"\n"
"fn div(x : Int, y : Int) -> Int raise DivError {\n"
"  if y == 0 {\n"
"    raise DivError(\"division by zero\")\n"
"  }\n"
"  x / y\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:82
msgid ""
"The `Error` can be used when the concrete error type is not important. For "
"convenience, you can omit the error type after the `raise` to indicate that "
"the `Error` type is used. For example, the following function signatures are"
" equivalent:"
msgstr ""
"具体的なエラー型が重要でない場合は `Error` を使えます。便宜上、`raise` の後のエラー型は省略でき、その場合は `Error` "
"型を使うことを意味します。例えば次の関数シグネチャは等価です:"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:87
msgid ""
"fn f() -> Unit raise {\n"
"  ...\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"fn g() -> Unit raise Error {\n"
"  let h : () -> Unit raise = fn() raise { fail(\"fail\") }\n"
"  ...\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"fn f() -> Unit raise {\n"
"  ...\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"fn g() -> Unit raise Error {\n"
"  let h : () -> Unit raise = fn() raise { fail(\"fail\") }\n"
"  ...\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:94
msgid ""
"For functions that are generic in the error type, you can use the `Error` "
"bound to do that. For example,"
msgstr "エラー型に対してジェネリックな関数では、`Error` 制約を使えます。例えば:"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:97
msgid ""
"// Result::unwrap_or_error\n"
"fn[T, E : Error] unwrap_or_error(result : Result[T, E]) -> T raise E {\n"
"  match result {\n"
"    Ok(x) => x\n"
"    Err(e) => raise e\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"// Result::unwrap_or_error\n"
"fn[T, E : Error] unwrap_or_error(result : Result[T, E]) -> T raise E {\n"
"  match result {\n"
"    Ok(x) => x\n"
"    Err(e) => raise e\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:103
msgid ""
"For functions that do not raise an error, you can add `noraise` in the "
"signature. For example:"
msgstr "エラーを送出しない関数には、シグネチャに `noraise` を追加できます。例えば:"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:106
msgid ""
"fn add(a : Int, b : Int) -> Int noraise {\n"
"  a + b\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"fn add(a : Int, b : Int) -> Int noraise {\n"
"  a + b\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:112
msgid "Error Polymorphism"
msgstr "エラー多相性"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:114
msgid ""
"It happens when a higher order function accepts another function as "
"parameter. The function as parameter may or may not throw error, which in "
"turn affects the behavior of this function."
msgstr "これは、高階関数が別の関数を引数として受け取るときに起こります。引数として渡される関数がエラーを送出する場合もしない場合もあり、それによってこの関数自身の振る舞いが変わります。"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:118
msgid "A notable example is `map` of `Array`:"
msgstr "代表的な例は `Array` の `map` です:"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:120
msgid ""
"fn[T] map(array : Array[T], f : (T) -> T raise) -> Array[T] raise {\n"
"  let mut res = []\n"
"  for x in array {\n"
"    res.push(f(x))\n"
"  }\n"
"  res\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"fn[T] map(array : Array[T], f : (T) -> T raise) -> Array[T] raise {\n"
"  let mut res = []\n"
"  for x in array {\n"
"    res.push(f(x))\n"
"  }\n"
"  res\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:126
msgid ""
"However, writing so would make the `map` function constantly having the "
"possibility of throwing errors, which is not the case."
msgstr "ただしこのように書くと、`map` 関数が常にエラーを送出する可能性を持つことになり、実態に合いません。"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:129
msgid ""
"Thus, the error polymorphism is introduced. You may use `raise?` to signify "
"that an error may or may not be throw."
msgstr "そこでエラー多相性が導入されています。`raise?` を使うと、エラーを送出する場合もしない場合もあることを表せます。"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:132
msgid ""
"fn[T] map_with_polymorphism(\n"
"  array : Array[T],\n"
"  f : (T) -> T raise?\n"
") -> Array[T] raise? {\n"
"  let mut res = []\n"
"  for x in array {\n"
"    res.push(f(x))\n"
"  }\n"
"  res\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"fn[T] map_without_error(\n"
"  array : Array[T],\n"
"  f : (T) -> T noraise,\n"
") -> Array[T] noraise {\n"
"  map_with_polymorphism(array, f)\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"fn[T] map_with_error(array : Array[T], f : (T) -> T raise) -> Array[T] raise"
" {\n"
"  map_with_polymorphism(array, f)\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"fn[T] map_with_polymorphism(\n"
"  array : Array[T],\n"
"  f : (T) -> T raise?\n"
") -> Array[T] raise? {\n"
"  let mut res = []\n"
"  for x in array {\n"
"    res.push(f(x))\n"
"  }\n"
"  res\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"fn[T] map_without_error(\n"
"  array : Array[T],\n"
"  f : (T) -> T noraise,\n"
") -> Array[T] noraise {\n"
"  map_with_polymorphism(array, f)\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"fn[T] map_with_error(array : Array[T], f : (T) -> T raise) -> Array[T] raise"
" {\n"
"  map_with_polymorphism(array, f)\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:138
msgid ""
"The signature of the `map_with_polymorphism` will be determined by the "
"actual parameter."
msgstr "`map_with_polymorphism` のシグネチャは、実際に渡される引数によって決定されます。"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:141
msgid "Handling Errors"
msgstr "エラー処理"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:143
msgid ""
"Applying the function normally will rethrow the error directly in case of an"
" error. For example:"
msgstr "関数を通常どおり呼び出すと、エラーが発生した場合はそのまま再送出されます。例えば:"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:146
msgid ""
"fn div_reraise(x : Int, y : Int) -> Int raise DivError {\n"
"  div(x, y) // Rethrow the error if `div` raised an error\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"fn div_reraise(x : Int, y : Int) -> Int raise DivError {\n"
"  div(x, y) // Rethrow the error if `div` raised an error\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:152
msgid "However, you may want to handle the errors."
msgstr "ただし、エラーをその場で処理したい場合もあります。"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:154
msgid "Try ... Catch"
msgstr "Try ... Catch"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:156
msgid "You can use `try` and `catch` to catch and handle errors, for example:"
msgstr "`try` と `catch` を使ってエラーを捕捉し、処理できます。例えば:"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:158
msgid ""
"fn main {\n"
"  try div(42, 0) catch {\n"
"    DivError(s) => println(s)\n"
"  } noraise {\n"
"    v => println(v)\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"fn main {\n"
"  try div(42, 0) catch {\n"
"    DivError(s) => println(s)\n"
"  } noraise {\n"
"    v => println(v)\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:166
msgid "Output"
msgstr "出力"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:166
msgid "division by zero\n"
msgstr "division by zero\n"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:170
msgid ""
"Here, `try` is used to call a function that might throw an error, and "
"`catch` is used to match and handle the caught error. If no error is caught,"
" the catch block will not be executed and the `noraise` block will be "
"executed instead."
msgstr ""
"ここでは、`try` でエラーを送出する可能性がある関数を呼び出し、`catch` "
"で捕捉したエラーをパターンマッチして処理しています。エラーが発生しなかった場合、`catch` ブロックは実行されず、代わりに `noraise` "
"ブロックが実行されます。"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:174
msgid ""
"The `noraise` block can be omitted if no action is needed when no error is "
"caught. For example:"
msgstr "エラーが発生しなかったときに何もしないなら、`noraise` ブロックは省略できます。例えば:"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:177
msgid ""
"try { println(div(42, 0)) } catch {\n"
"  _ => println(\"Error\")\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"try { println(div(42, 0)) } catch {\n"
"  _ => println(\"Error\")\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:184
msgid ""
"When the body of `try` is a simple expression, the curly braces, and even "
"the `try` keyword can be omitted. For example:"
msgstr "`try` の本体が単純な式である場合は、中括弧、さらには `try` キーワード自体も省略できます。例えば:"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:187
msgid ""
"let a = div(42, 0) catch { _ => 0 }\n"
"println(a)\n"
msgstr ""
"let a = div(42, 0) catch { _ => 0 }\n"
"println(a)\n"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:194
msgid "Transforming to Result"
msgstr "Result への変換"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:196
msgid ""
"You can also catch the potential error and transform into a first-class "
"value of the [`Result`](/language/fundamentals.md#option-and-result) type, "
"by using `try?` before an expression that may throw error:"
msgstr ""
"エラーを送出する可能性のある式の前に `try?` を付けると、潜在的なエラーを捕捉して "
"[`Result`](/language/fundamentals.md#option-and-result) 型の first-class "
"な値へ変換することもできます:"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:200
msgid ""
"test {\n"
"  let res = try? (div(6, 0) * div(6, 3))\n"
"  inspect(\n"
"    res,\n"
"    content=(\n"
"      #|Err(\"division by zero\")\n"
"    ),\n"
"  )\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"test {\n"
"  let res = try? (div(6, 0) * div(6, 3))\n"
"  inspect(\n"
"    res,\n"
"    content=(\n"
"      #|Err(\"division by zero\")\n"
"    ),\n"
"  )\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:206
msgid "Panic on Errors"
msgstr "エラー時にパニックする"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:208
msgid "You can also panic directly when an unexpected error occurs:"
msgstr "予期しないエラーが起きたときに直接パニックさせることもできます:"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:210
msgid ""
"fn remainder(a : Int, b : Int) -> Int raise DivError {\n"
"  if b == 0 {\n"
"    raise DivError(\"division by zero\")\n"
"  }\n"
"  let div = try! div(a, b)\n"
"  a - b * div\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"fn remainder(a : Int, b : Int) -> Int raise DivError {\n"
"  if b == 0 {\n"
"    raise DivError(\"division by zero\")\n"
"  }\n"
"  let div = try! div(a, b)\n"
"  a - b * div\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:216
msgid "Error Inference"
msgstr "エラー推論"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:218
msgid ""
"Within a `try` block, several different kinds of errors can be raised. When "
"that happens, the compiler will use the type `Error` as the common error "
"type. Accordingly, the handler must use the wildcard `_` to make sure all "
"errors are caught, and `e => raise e` to reraise the other errors. For "
"example,"
msgstr ""
"`try` ブロック内では、複数種類のエラーが送出されることがあります。その場合、コンパイラは共通エラー型として `Error` "
"型を使います。したがってハンドラ側では、すべてのエラーを捕捉するためにワイルドカード `_` を使い、`e => raise e` "
"で他のエラーを再送出する必要があります。例えば:"

#: ../../language/error-handling.md:223
msgid ""
"fn f1() -> Unit raise E1 {\n"
"  ...\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"fn f2() -> Unit raise E2 {\n"
"  ...\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"try {\n"
"  f1()\n"
"  f2()\n"
"} catch {\n"
"  E1(_) => ...\n"
"  E2 => ...\n"
"  e => raise e\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"fn f1() -> Unit raise E1 {\n"
"  ...\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"fn f2() -> Unit raise E2 {\n"
"  ...\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"try {\n"
"  f1()\n"
"  f2()\n"
"} catch {\n"
"  E1(_) => ...\n"
"  E2 => ...\n"
"  e => raise e\n"
"}\n"

